Jabba Desilijic Tiure, better known as Jabba the Hutt, is one of the most notorious Hutt crime lords in the galaxy, who governs a large criminal empire located in the Outer Rim Territories from his desert palace on Tatooine.

Jabba had started as a small crime lord, but quickly spread his influence into a variety of illegal activities, including spice-smuggling, gunrunning, slavery, and sometimes outright piracy. Known for his cruelty and carnal fancies, Jabba the Hutt is powerful enough not to fear Alliance retributions, and placed a hefty death mark on Han Solo, a former employee of his, after Solo lost a load of spice to an Imperial patrol vessel.

A Zabrak improvement on the combat suit, this armor is good protection where speed and unrestricted movement are more important than bulky plating.

There are a variety of different kinds of armor intended to defend against the harsh enviroments of space, deflect the impact of blaster bolts and protect versus all types of damage that can be found on a battlefield. These suits are usually built in with a personal shield generator.

The BlasTech DL-22 Blaster Pistol is designed as a response to the MerrSonn DD6 weapon. The gun's barrel used a higher-grade focusing crystal to increase the damage dealt by the weapon's blasts, at the expense of the gun's stun setting. The DL-22 is held in high regard by those who prefer to customize their weapons.

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.

The Raptors are a gang in the undercity of Coruscant. Their main territory is in the Crimson Corridor, and their membership includes Humans, Kubaz, Bith, Gotals, Snivvians, Trandoshans, Saurin, Devaronians, and H'nemthe.

Power paks or power cells provide energy for many vehicles, and small blaster weapons. Most power cells contain concentrated amounts of gases that, when heated, form plasma. In small blasters, power cells are used to create blaster bolts that are not nearly as powerful as blasters using a combination of magazines containing gases (that after being heated would change into plasma) and proper Blaster power packs. A small power cell could be used to power a prosthetic without the need for recharging.

This holdout blaster pistol, sometimes known as a scout blaster, is a standard-issue weapon used by the scout troopers of the Galactic Empire. Clone scout troopers of the 41st Elite Legion were also known to carry these weapons during the latter stages of the Clone Wars.

This compact, one-handed blaster is fitted with a side-mounted targeting scope and phase amplifier, and featured a miniature gas cell on the rear. The weapon had a short-range barrel. Scout troopers commonly carry these weapons in a boot holster. Because scout troopers wore padded gloves, the pistol has a pressure-sensitive stock rather than a trigger. The trooper is able to grip the stock with two gloved fingers through the enlarged finger guard.

The EE-3 carbine rifle is a blaster that was modeled after the E-11 blaster rifle used by Imperial Stormtroopers. The rifle consisted of a small handle attached to a long circular barrel. An alternate version of this model features a modified scope mounting and hand grips that run the length of the barrel.

The EE-3 was used famously by the bounty hunter Boba Fett. Fett modified his by adding a stock and an electronic scope for sniping, making it a dangerous weapon. Prince Xizor also used an EE-3 to try to kill Luke Skywalker as the Jedi and his friends escaped the Falleen's palace on Coruscant.

The A280 is a blaster rifle produced by BlasTech Industries and is considered to be one of the best armor-piercing blasters produced.

Though much heavier than Imperial-issue rifles such as the E-11, the A280 is a sturdy weapon and is reputed to be able to cut a fully-armored stormtrooper in half at medium range. This weapon, along with its predecessor, the DLT-20A, were marketed as Longblasters. The A280 was different from the DLT-20A in that its galven circuits were clustered near the focusing crystal, giving the weapon a slight bulge at the midsection. This also provided the A280 with more power over a longer range.

Gamorrean guards were Gamorreans under the employ of an organization, for the purpose of defending or blocking something. These guards were usually in a shady occupation, in the employ of a crimelord or criminal syndicate. They were favored over other species for the job because of their demeanor and size. However, before working for their employers, their customs demanded that they test his or her honor and skill in hand-to-hand combat.

The Gamorrean War Axe is an inert, traditional precursor to the vibro-axes, such as the Arg'garok, often used by Gamorrean warriors. Nonetheless, the weapon is capable of inflicting considerable damage on an enemy.

Blue milk, sometimes known as Bantha milk is a blue-colored liquid produced by a female bantha's mammary glands. It can be found on most planets across the galaxy. The milk is well known for being very rich and  refreshing, its opaque coloring suggesting that it is also sweet. The milk is also used to make a variety of yogurt, ice cream, and cheese. Its ubiquity inspired the military phrase blue milk run.
